_notice() {
  cat <<'EOF'

Sotto is installed. Two one-time steps for the global push-to-talk hotkey:

  1. Add your user to the `input` group so Sotto can read the keyboard:

         sudo usermod -aG input "$USER"

     Then log out and back in (or reboot) for it to take effect.

  2. Typing into apps uses a backend matched to your session:
       - X11 ...................... xdotool   (installed)
       - Wayland (wlroots/KDE) .... wtype     (installed)
       - GNOME-Wayland ............ install `ydotool` and run ydotoold; or use an X11 session

On first launch, open Settings → Model & language → Download (one-time, ~300 MB).
Then hold Ctrl+Super, speak, and release. Enjoy!

EOF
}

post_install() {
  _notice
}

post_upgrade() {
  _notice
}
